category: SCIENTISTS AS PARENTS
category comment: 

clue: Behave or I'll turn this car around right now! This many degrees--half a circle; don't think I won't

response: 180

clue: If you sit that close to the TV & burn this eye part that receives images from the lens, don't come running to me

response: the retina

clue: When you have daughters of your own, with this chromosomal letter pair, you'll understand

response: XX

clue: Keep making that face & it'll freeze that way... absolute zero, mister! On this scale named for a British scientist

response: (Lord) Kelvin

clue: Why is this & not oxygen the most abundant element in the Earth's atmosphere? Because, I said so!

response: nitrogen

